# Vec<T, A>

A contiguous growable array type, written as `Vec<T>`.

## Examples

```rust
let mut vec = Vec::new();
vec.push(1);
vec.push(2);
assert_eq!(vec.len(), 2);
assert_eq!(vec[0], 1);
```

